<div class="quotetitle">Jcee wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;">hmm, the color option should tint it to a similar color as the theme color you get when you rightclick the desktop and choose personalize, then click color. Are you saying this isnt the case &#40;aka if you were to choose red and add color it wouldnt give the menu a red tint&#41;? If it is for some reason picking a color based on one of your previous task-bar colors and not your current one, my only guess would be classic shell for some reason isnt updating this information any more; try restarting classic start menu.exe running it as an admin, see if that fixes anything. otherwise post a screenshot, and ill see if we can get to the bottom of this </span></span></span><img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt="" />&quot;%20title=&quot;Razz&quot;%20style=&quot;margin:%200px;%20padding:%200px;%20border:%20none;%20color:%20rgb(50,%2061,%2079);%20font-family:%20'Lucida%20Grande',%20'Trebuchet%20MS',%20Helvetica,%20Arial,%20sans-serif;%20font-size:%2012.800000190734863px;%20line-height:%2018.200000762939453px;%20background-color:%20rgb(236,%20236,%20236);[/img]<span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;"> thanks</span></span></span><br /><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;">im aware that there are some deviations with color intensity option between w7 and w8, which is the main reason for dark/gray/white options, because dark is generally better with w7/darker themes/taskbar colors, and light generally fits w8 better.</span></span></span><br /><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;">also glad to hear you still like/use it, ive been tempted &#40;when i remade all the resources with light/dark/gray variation&#41; to just dump the option altogether &#40;or limit it to a single variation&#41;</span></span></span><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;"><br /></span></span></span><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;">UPDATE: Removed the custom image option, although all the code is still there, you just have to remove the ; by it, and re-add a resource 31. mostly because it tripled the skins size just to have it <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />, and i probably will make a breakaway skin. </span></span></span><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#ececec;">Also added a bitmap mask to make the edges more defined when using the &#39;add color&#39; option</span></span></span><br /></div><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Tried the 3/31 version &amp; everything is fine now--add color now replicates the taskbar color in the menu.  Thanks again!<br /><br />Any thoughts on how Win&quot;8.1&quot; is going to affect Classic Menu?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=458">waltc</a> — Tue Jun 04, 2013 12:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
